<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<task id="AIPL-010" project="AI Platform Foundation Phase 1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement RagQueryBuilder — Metadata-Aware RAG Query Strategy</title>
    <phase>2 — Workstream A: Retrieval Foundation</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, api, foundation, retrieval</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPL-004</dependencies>
    <blocks>AIPL-015 (KnowledgeBaseEndpoints), AIPL-017 (retrieval instrumentation)</blocks>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Replace the existing first-500-characters RAG query approach in AnalysisOrchestrationService
    with a metadata-aware RagQueryBuilder. The builder constructs targeted queries from
    DocumentAnalysisResult metadata (entities, key phrases, document type, section titles) to
    dramatically improve retrieval relevance.

    The existing RagService.cs performs vector search but uses a naive query. RagQueryBuilder
    sits between AnalysisOrchestrationService and RagService, building a richer query from
    the analysis result context before vector search executes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer familiar with Azure AI Search vector search, RAG patterns,
    and the existing Spaarke AI orchestration pipeline.
  </role>

  <goal>
    RagQueryBuilder.cs is implemented and registered in DI. AnalysisOrchestrationService uses
    it to build queries. Unit tests pass. Build succeeds with 0 errors.
  </goal>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Register as concrete type: services.AddSingleton&lt;RagQueryBuilder&gt;()</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">All retrieval logic stays in BFF — no separate retrieval service</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Queries must be tenant-scoped; include tenantId in filter expressions</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">Must use DocumentAnalysisResult metadata fields: entities, keyPhrases, documentType, sectionTitles</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-platform-enhancements-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs</file>
      <file>docs/guides/RAG-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/RAG-CONFIGURATION.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read existing RAG code">
      Read AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs and RagService.cs to understand current query construction
      and how the first-500-chars approach is used. Note the method signatures.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Create RagQueryBuilder.cs">
      Create src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagQueryBuilder.cs:
      - Method: BuildQuery(DocumentAnalysisResult result, string tenantId) → RagQuery
      - Extract: entities (top 5 by relevance), keyPhrases (top 10), documentType, sectionTitles
      - Combine into semantic search text with entity emphasis
      - Add tenant filter expression for Azure AI Search
      - Add document type filter if strongly typed (e.g., "NDA", "Lease")
      - RagQuery record: { SearchText, FilterExpression, Top, MinRelevanceScore }
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Update RagService to accept RagQuery">
      Modify RagService.cs to accept RagQuery parameter instead of raw string.
      Keep backward-compatible overload if needed by other callers.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Update AnalysisOrchestrationService">
      Inject RagQueryBuilder into AnalysisOrchestrationService.
      Replace first-500-chars call with: var query = _ragQueryBuilder.BuildQuery(result, tenantId)
      Pass query to RagService.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Register in Program.cs">
      Add: builder.Services.AddSingleton&lt;RagQueryBuilder&gt;();
      Verify DI count stays within ADR-010 budget (update CLAUDE.md count).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Write unit tests">
      Create tests/unit/Services/Ai/RagQueryBuilderTests.cs:
      - Test: entities extracted from result appear in search text
      - Test: tenant filter expression contains tenantId
      - Test: document type filter applied when type is known
      - Test: empty result produces reasonable fallback query
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify build and tests">
      Run: dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/
      Run: dotnet test tests/unit/ --filter "RagQueryBuilder"
      Both must pass with 0 errors.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build and test</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage changes</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagQueryBuilder.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RagService.cs (modified)</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/AnalysisOrchestrationService.cs (modified)</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs (registration added)</output>
    <output type="test">tests/unit/Services/Ai/RagQueryBuilderTests.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">RagQueryBuilder.BuildQuery() returns a query using entity + keyphrase metadata</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">AnalysisOrchestrationService no longer uses first-500-chars approach</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unit tests pass (4 test cases minimum)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">dotnet build succeeds with 0 errors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">DI count in CLAUDE.md updated</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
